A sorted vector is given, with different elements. Is there an index i such that v[i] = i? Elements can be negative too

Input:
vector

Output:
index i with v[i] = i

Solution:

The vector is sorted, so binary search can be applied to it. if (v[mid] - i < 0), the solution is to the right, otherwise if (v[mid] - i > 0), the solution is to the left, otherwise the solution is the element.
We use a 0-indexed vector, a left and a right index. The scheme used is Divide et Impera through a binary search.

Complexity:

T: O(logn) // binary search halves the search interval each time
S: O(1) // no auxiliary DS used